# Intuition
- First of all, to merge in one of the given array, we have to iterate from end
- Which of the element is larger than other in the given array than we have to place it at the end of the first array.
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
- Creating three variables

        - int i=m-1;
        - int j=n-1;
        - int k=nums1.length-1;

- We have to check i & j is greater than zero,

        if(i>=0 && j>=0) 

- Then check the last Element of i & j which is greater

 (NOTE: i=(m-1) not last index bcoz we already have extra space to fill ) 

       if(nums1[i]>nums2[j]){
           nums1[k]=nums1[i];
           k--;
           i--;
        }else{
           nums1[k]=nums2[j];
           k--;
           j--;
       }


In this way, reducing i & j we iterate from last to first element & add all the sorted elements in Nums1[i] 
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(m + n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

