1. **Atmost 1 Transaction - Kadane's algorithm**

```
 public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {
        int maxEndingHere = 0;
		int maxSoFar = 0;
		for (int i = 1; i < prices.length; i++) {
			maxEndingHere = Math.max(0, maxEndingHere+prices[i] - prices[i - 1]);
			maxSoFar = Math.max(maxSoFar, maxEndingHere);
		}
		return maxSoFar;
    }
```
Time : O(n)
Space: O(1)

**2. Infinite Transactions**
	If you have increase in price compared to previous price, add it to profit
```
 public int maxProfit(int[] prices) {
        int profit = 0;
		for (int i = 0; i < prices.length - 1; i++) {
			if (prices[i + 1] > prices[i]) {
				profit += prices[i+1] - prices[i];
			}
		}
		return profit;
    }
```
Time : O(n)
Space: O(1)

**3. Atmost K Transactions**
The third & fourth requires DP & are almost the same. If you solve for generic K, you can use the same for specfic K=2.

