```
DP: 
dp[i][j] = Max(dp[i][j-1],prices[j]-prices[m]+dp[i-1][m])
m = 0..j-1

dp[i][j-1]                     -> if you are not making a transaction on day j
prices[j]-prices[m]+dp[i-1][m] -> if you are making a transaction on day j, find the m th day to buy the stock 
i = no of transactions
j = prices.length

Time: O(k * n * n) 
Space: O(k * n) 
k = K transactions
n = prices.length
```
**Optimized DP** 
```
maxDiff = Max(maxDiff,dp[i-1][j-1] - prices[j-1])
dp[i][j] = Max(dp[i][j-1],prices[j]+maxDiff)

dp[i][j-1]                     -> if you are not making a transaction on day j
prices[j]-prices[m]+dp[i-1][m] -> if you are making a transaction on day j, compute the maxDiff from 0 ..j-1. In other words, we are reusing the maxDiff computed before. This reduces O(n) time complexity 

Time: O(k * n) 
Space: O(k * n) 
k = K transactions
n = prices.length
```
