solutions.content:
This question unifies this series of problems. 

[121. Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock](https://leetcode.com/problems/best-time-to-buy-and-sell-stock/discuss/695515/Python3-two-approaches)
[122. Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock II](https://leetcode.com/problems/best-time-to-buy-and-sell-stock-ii/discuss/702615/Python3-1-line)
[123. Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock III](https://leetcode.com/problems/best-time-to-buy-and-sell-stock-iii/discuss/702602/Python3-two-approaches)

Recall that in [121. Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock](https://leetcode.com/problems/best-time-to-buy-and-sell-stock/discuss/695515/Python3-two-approaches), there are two approaches 
1) buy low & sell high;
2) Kadane's algorithm.

Both approaches could be generalized into cases with multiple transactions, say `K`. 

**Approach 1 -- buy low & sell high** (`O(NK)` time & `O(K)` space)

```
class Solution:
    def maxProfit(self, k: int, prices: List[int]) -> int:
        if k >= len(prices)//2: return sum(max(0, prices[i] - prices[i-1]) for i in range(1, len(prices)))
        buy, sell = [inf]*k, [0]*k
        for x in prices:
            for i in range(k):
                if i: buy[i] = min(buy[i], x - sell[i-1])
                else: buy[i] = min(buy[i], x)
                sell[i] = max(sell[i], x - buy[i])
        return sell[-1] if k and prices else 0
```

**Approach 2 -- Kadane's algo**
The second approach is to extend Kadane's algorithm to the cases with multiple transaction (`O(NK)` time & `O(N)` space)

```
class Solution:
    def maxProfit(self, k: int, prices: List[int]) -> int:
        if k >= len(prices)//2: return sum(max(0, prices[i] - prices[i-1]) for i in range(1, len(prices)))
        ans = [0]*len(prices)
        for _ in range(k):
            most = 0
            for i in range(1, len(prices)):
                most = max(ans[i], most + prices[i] - prices[i-1])
                ans[i] = max(ans[i-1], most)
        return ans[-1]
```

