Before reading this, I suggest you have a try for https://leetcode.com/problems/best-time-to-buy-and-sell-stock-iii/
first.

Most of the solutions I found are using two status: buy and sell, and maintain the max profit for both, which I somehow found abstract and difficult to understand. If you also think so, this solution may help you understand the question from another perspective.

This is my ans to it:
it is obvious that in this question profit = price - cost. So we just need to store the min cost before curernt day, and sell it at the highest price to get the max profit for the 1st transaction.

And for the second transaction, we need a find another minimum cost, meanwhile keeping the profit from 1st transaction as maximum.
To satisfy this we can just use min(price - profit1) as min cost2.

```
var maxProfit = function(prices) {
    let cost1 = prices[0];
    let cost2 = prices[0];
    let profit1 = 0;
    let profit2 = 0;

    for(let i = 1; i < prices.length; i++){
        profit1 = Math.max(profit1, prices[i] - cost1);
        profit2 = Math.max(profit2, prices[i] - cost2);

        cost1 = Math.min(cost1, prices[i]);
        cost2 = Math.min(cost2, prices[i] - profit1);
    }

    return profit2;
};
```

Now back to this question. Let's say we have k = 3. Can we modify the solution above to get the ans?

very simple. we just copy and paste a set of codes for transaction3:
```
var maxProfit = function(prices) {
    let cost1 = prices[0];
    let cost2 = prices[0];
	let cost3 = prices[0];

    let profit1 = 0;
    let profit2 = 0;
	let profit3 = 0;

    for(let i = 1; i < prices.length; i++){
        profit1 = Math.max(profit1, prices[i] - cost1);
        profit2 = Math.max(profit2, prices[i] - cost2);
		profit3 = Math.max(profit3, prices[i] - cost3);

        cost1 = Math.min(cost1, prices[i]);
        cost2 = Math.min(cost2, prices[i] - profit1);
		cost3 = Math.min(cost3, prices[i] - profit2);
    }

    return profit3;
};
```

One point we observe is that, to determine the min cost for transaction[k], we need to know the profit of transaction[k-1]. 

Now we convert the copy and paste parts into arrays and a loop. 

```
var maxProfit = function(k, prices) {
    if(prices.length <= 1) return 0;

	//as we are now using arrays, we also store "cost0" and "profit0" for easier coding. So we need have k+1 elements.
    let costs = Array(k+1).fill(Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER);
    let profits = Array(k+1).fill(0);

    profits[0] = 0;
    costs[0] = prices[0];

    for(let i = 0; i < prices.length; i++){
        for(let j = 1; j <= k; j++){
            profits[j] = Math.max(profits[j], prices[i] - costs[j]);  
            costs[j] = Math.min(costs[j], prices[i] - profits[j-1]);
        }
    }

	//from the above loop we also maintain the max profits[k] with different i. So we can just return profits[k].
    return profits[k];
};
```

