Inspired by amazing solution from Stock III by *weijiac*, shout out to him!
https://leetcode.com/problems/best-time-to-buy-and-sell-stock-iii/solutions/39611/is-it-best-solution-with-o-n-o-1/

Basically we are keeping track of highest profit for each k, starting from 1 and ending with k transactions, each transaction is only feasible if the last transaction is completed.

```C++ []
class Solution {
public:
    int maxProfit(int k, vector<int>& prices) {
        vector<int> sell(k+1, 0), bought(k+1, INT_MIN);
        for(auto price: prices) {
            for(int i=k-1; i>=0; --i){
                sell[i] = max(sell[i], bought[i] + price);
                bought[i] = max(bought[i], i == 0 ? -price : sell[i-1]-price);
            }
        }
        return sell[k-1];
    }
};
```

