the same as [123. Best Time to Buy and Sell Stock III](https://leetcode.com/problems/best-time-to-buy-and-sell-stock-iii/)
to calculate the sell[j], we only need the sell[j-1] and buy[j-1]
If the jth sell we have two choice:
* 	1. we don't do anything, have the same profit of the j-1th day.
* 	2. or we sell in the jth day.

then it would be 
sell[j] = max(sell[j-1], prices[i] + buy[j-1]);
buy[j] = max(buy[j-1], sell[j-1] - prices[i]);

if we caculate in 1 to k
we need a extra space to store the last day of buy and sell, because it will change when we caculate.
if we calculate in reverse and we only need the buy[j-1] and sell[j-1].  
we can use sell[j] and buy[j] to store.
sell[j] would be sell[j-1] before it change.
buy[j] would be buy[j-1] before it change.

