solutions.content:
**Idea?**
* Maintain **buy[i][j]** and **sell[i][j]** where *buy[i][j]* denotes maximum profit we can have if we perform atmost j transactions with first i items and considering the last transaction is buying the stock.
* Similarly, *sell[i][j]* denotes maximum profit we can have if we perform atmost j transactions with first i items and considering the last transaction is selling the stock.
* Transition states for buying is :- **buy[i][j] = max(sell[i-1][j-1]-prices[i-1],buy[i-1][j])**, buy the stock right now (so previous stock must be sold earlier) or don't buy.
* Transition states for selling is :-  **sell[i][j] = max(buy[i-1][j]+prices[i-1],sell[i-1][j])**, sell the stock right now (so previous stock must be bought earlier) or don't sell.
* Check code.
```
class Solution {
public:
    // Time Complexity:- O(NK)
    // Space Complexity:- O(NK)
    int maxProfit(vector<int>& prices) {
        int n = prices.size(),k = 2;
        vector<vector<int>> buy(n+1,vector<int>(k+1,INT_MIN));
        vector<vector<int>> sell(n+1,vector<int>(k+1,INT_MIN));
        for(int i=0;i<=n;i++)
            sell[i][0] = 0;
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
            for(int j=1;j<=k;j++){
                // buy this stock in jth transaction
                if(sell[i-1][j-1]!=INT_MIN)
                    buy[i][j] = max(buy[i][j],sell[i-1][j-1]-prices[i-1]);
                // don't buy this stock in jth transaction
                buy[i][j] = max(buy[i][j],buy[i-1][j]);

                // sell this stock in jth transaction
                if(buy[i-1][j]!=INT_MIN)
                    sell[i][j] = max(sell[i][j],buy[i-1][j]+prices[i-1]);
                // don't sell this stock in jth transaction
                sell[i][j] = max(sell[i][j],sell[i-1][j]);
            }
        }
        int ans = 0;
        for(int j=0;j<=k;j++)
            ans = max(ans,sell[n][j]);
        return ans;
    }
};
```
