# Understanding the problem


The stock trading problems presented involve an array of stock prices, where each element represents the price of the stock on a given day. The objective is to determine the maximum profit that can be obtained by performing a series of buy and sell transactions, subject to certain constraints. These constraints may include *transaction fees*, *cooldown periods*, or a *maximum number of transactions allowed*.


